info.name: NovaCept Transfer
info.description:
The Novacept API methods.

The "x-api-key" parameter in all headers should be set to your API Key provided by the Novacept system to you.

All modules include "Ping" method to test the module.

The followings are the values for the parameters in all methods.

## SortingOrder Options:

1. ASC
2. DESC
    

## PageNumber Options:

Must be a number more than 1 that indicate the page number for the pagination of all methods.

## RecordsPerPage Options:

Must be a number more than 1 that indicate the records per page for the pagination of all methods. For most methods this parameter must be less than 100.

item.name: Root
Authentication

request.description:
Use this method to login using this method and get the token that will be used in the other methods.

The TokenLifeTime is the time that the token is valid, it's in minutes. For example 720 minutes.
To invalidate the token you should call the logout method.

item.description: All user management methods are in this folder. You can login or register a new user using these methods.
User Management and ErrorCodes methods are available in this module.
